[FILE:572:descriptions/desc.primary]
The GLE Tubing and Extrusion Library is a graphics application programming 
interface (API). The library consists of a number of "C" language 
subroutines for drawing tubing and extrusions. It is a very fast 
implementation of these shapes, outperforming all other implementations, 
most by orders of magnitude. The library is distributed in source code 
form, in a package that includes documentation, a VRML proposal, 
Makefiles, and full source code and header files. It uses the OpenGL (TM) 
programming API to perform the actual drawing of the tubing and extrusions.


